## CommandContext Location

`CommandContext` is defined in `crates/kanban-domain/src/commands/mod.rs` (not context.rs). It holds flat `Vec` references:

```rust
pub struct CommandContext<'a> {
    pub boards: &'a mut Vec<Board>,
    pub columns: &'a mut Vec<Column>,
    pub cards: &'a mut Vec<Card>,
    pub sprints: &'a mut Vec<Sprint>,
    pub archived_cards: &'a mut Vec<ArchivedCard>,
    pub graph: &'a mut DependencyGraph,
}
```

Currently has **no helper methods** — all lookups are inline `iter_mut().find(...)`.

## Step 1 — Add Helper Methods to CommandContext

Add these 5 methods to the `CommandContext` impl block in `crates/kanban-domain/src/commands/mod.rs`:

```rust
impl<'a> CommandContext<'a> {
    pub fn get_board_mut(&mut self, id: Uuid) -> KanbanResult<&mut Board> {
        self.boards.iter_mut().find(|b| b.id == id)
            .ok_or_else(|| KanbanError::NotFound(format\!("Board {}", id)))
    }

    pub fn get_card_mut(&mut self, id: Uuid) -> KanbanResult<&mut Card> {
        self.cards.iter_mut().find(|c| c.id == id)
            .ok_or_else(|| KanbanError::NotFound(format\!("Card {}", id)))
    }

    pub fn get_column_mut(&mut self, id: Uuid) -> KanbanResult<&mut Column> {
        self.columns.iter_mut().find(|c| c.id == id)
            .ok_or_else(|| KanbanError::NotFound(format\!("Column {}", id)))
    }

    pub fn get_sprint_mut(&mut self, id: Uuid) -> KanbanResult<&mut Sprint> {
        self.sprints.iter_mut().find(|s| s.id == id)
            .ok_or_else(|| KanbanError::NotFound(format\!("Sprint {}", id)))
    }

    pub fn get_archived_card_mut(&mut self, card_id: Uuid) -> KanbanResult<&mut ArchivedCard> {
        self.archived_cards.iter_mut().find(|ac| ac.card.id == card_id)
            .ok_or_else(|| KanbanError::NotFound(format\!("Archived card {}", card_id)))
    }
}
```

