## Context

When the TUI is running, internal warnings from the `tracing` crate appear as raw text inline in the terminal interface. Example from screenshot:

```
026-04-18T04:58:21.227836Z  WARN kanban_tui::app: Could not spawn save worker: no store available
```

This appears mid-screen, overlapping the rendered UI, making the app look broken.

## Root cause

**Tracing writes to stderr while ratatui owns the terminal.**

The tracing subscriber is configured in `crates/kanban-cli/src/app.rs` `init_tracing()`:

```rust
// Default mode (no KANBAN_DEBUG_LOG env var):
let fmt_layer = tracing_subscriber::fmt::layer()
    .with_writer(std::io::stderr)   // ← writes directly to terminal
    .with_filter(LevelFilter::WARN);
```

ratatui enters alternate screen mode via `EnterAlternateScreen`, which renders to a dedicated terminal buffer. But stderr writes bypass this buffer entirely. Any `tracing::warn!()` or `tracing::error!()` call produces raw text that corrupts the TUI.

The app does have a user-facing error system — `App::set_error(msg)` creates a `Banner` overlay that auto-clears after 3 seconds. But internal warnings use `tracing::warn!()` instead, which leaks to stderr.

