## Proposed solution

### Step 1 — Add the helper

```rust
// crates/kanban-tui/src/app/mod.rs (next to other helper methods on App)

impl App {
    /// Runs a board-scoped command if the user is on the card view
    /// with an active board. The closure receives the active board
    /// and returns the command to execute (or None to no-op silently).
    ///
    /// Errors from `execute_command` are surfaced via the standard
    /// `tracing::error!` + `set_error` banner pair.
    pub(crate) fn execute_board_command<F>(&mut self, build: F)
    where
        F: FnOnce(&Board) -> Option<Command>,
    {
        if self.focus.active != Focus::Cards {
            return;
        }
        let Some(idx) = self.selection.active_board_index else { return };
        let board = match self.model.boards().get(idx) {
            Some(b) => b.clone(),  // clone keeps the borrow scope tight
            None => return,
        };
        let Some(cmd) = build(&board) else { return };
        if let Err(e) = self.execute_command(cmd) {
            tracing::error!("Command failed: {}", e);
            self.set_error(format!("Command failed: {}", e));
        }
    }
}
```

The clone of `Board` is acceptable — boards are small structs. The alternative (carrying a borrow into the closure) fights the borrow checker for no gain.

