# Section: UndoStack → kanban-core

kanban-service's `UndoStack` (crates/kanban-service/src/undo_stack.rs, 221 lines incl. tests) is pure cursor-and-vec bookkeeping. The only kanban-specific bit is `use kanban_domain::commands::Command;` at the top — `UndoEntry { forward: Vec<Command>, inverse: Vec<Command> }` names it. Parameterize on `Cmd` and the whole module moves to core verbatim.

## Suggested design

`crates/kanban-core/src/undo.rs`:

```rust
use crate::Command;

#[derive(Debug, Clone)]
pub struct UndoEntry<Cmd: Command> {
    pub forward: Vec<Cmd>,
    pub inverse: Vec<Cmd>,
}

#[derive(Debug, Clone)]
pub struct UndoStack<Cmd: Command> {
    entries: Vec<UndoEntry<Cmd>>,
    cursor: usize,
}

impl<Cmd: Command> Default for UndoStack<Cmd> {
    fn default() -> Self { Self { entries: Vec::new(), cursor: 0 } }
}

impl<Cmd: Command> UndoStack<Cmd> {
    pub fn new() -> Self { Self::default() }
    pub fn push(&mut self, entry: UndoEntry<Cmd>) { /* unchanged */ }
    pub fn peek_undo(&self) -> Option<&UndoEntry<Cmd>> { /* unchanged */ }
    pub fn peek_redo(&self) -> Option<&UndoEntry<Cmd>> { /* unchanged */ }
    pub fn commit_undo(&mut self) -> bool { /* unchanged */ }
    pub fn commit_redo(&mut self) -> bool { /* unchanged */ }
    pub fn clear(&mut self) { /* unchanged */ }
    pub fn undo_depth(&self) -> usize { /* unchanged */ }
    pub fn redo_depth(&self) -> usize { /* unchanged */ }
    pub fn can_undo(&self) -> bool { /* unchanged */ }
    pub fn can_redo(&self) -> bool { /* unchanged */ }
}
```

Method bodies port byte-identical. The `Default` impl is hand-written because `Cmd: Default` isn't a reasonable bound.

After the move, `kanban-service/src/context.rs` changes one field declaration (`undo_stack: kanban_core::UndoStack<Command>`) and one constructor reference. All existing method calls (`self.undo_stack.peek_undo()` etc.) keep working because the API surface is identical.

## Alternatives considered

- **Generic `UndoStack<Cmd>` in core (CHOSEN)**: minimal change, exact API parity, eight existing tests port with a one-line `TestCmd` fake substitution.
- **Type alias `pub type UndoStack = UndoStack<Command>` in service for backward compat**: only worth doing if external imports exist. Grep first; current state is internal-only `mod undo_stack;` so the alias isn't needed.
- **Skip the `Cmd: Command` bound and use `PhantomData`**: adds complexity. We do need `Cmd: Clone` (push semantics) and `Cmd: Send + Sync` (Context threading); easier to inherit those via `Cmd: Command`.

