# Define the generic Backend trait in kanban-core

## Motivation
First concrete step of the Backend section. Create `crates/kanban-core/src/backend.rs` (placeholder created in Scaffolding section) with the abstract `Backend` trait. No callers wire through it yet — that's downstream cards.

## Current state
Placeholder file exists from Scaffolding section. `kanban-core/Cargo.toml` already has `async-trait`, `uuid`, `thiserror` (no new deps needed).

## Target shape
```rust
//! Generic storage-backend abstraction.
//!
//! `Backend` is the lifecycle contract every storage layer satisfies.
//! Domain-flavoured CRUD lives on consumer-side extension traits
//! (e.g. `kanban_service::KanbanBackend: Backend + DataStore + CommandStore`).

use async_trait::async_trait;
use uuid::Uuid;
use crate::{CoreError, CoreResult};

#[async_trait]
pub trait Backend: Send + Sync {
    /// Aggregate snapshot type for default `with_transaction` rollback.
    /// Disk-backed backends with native transactions can use `type Snapshot = ()`
    /// and override `with_transaction`.
    type Snapshot: Send;

    fn snapshot(&self) -> CoreResult<Self::Snapshot>;
    fn apply_snapshot(&self, snapshot: Self::Snapshot) -> CoreResult<()>;

    async fn flush(&self) -> CoreResult<()> { Ok(()) }
    async fn reload(&self) -> CoreResult<()> { Ok(()) }
    fn needs_flush(&self) -> bool { false }
    fn needs_save_worker(&self) -> bool { false }
    fn instance_id(&self) -> Uuid { Uuid::nil() }

    fn with_transaction(
        &self,
        f: &mut dyn FnMut() -> CoreResult<()>,
    ) -> CoreResult<()> {
        let before = self.snapshot()?;
        match f() {
            Ok(()) => Ok(()),
            Err(e) => {
                if let Err(rollback_err) = self.apply_snapshot(before) {
                    return Err(CoreError::Internal(format!(
                        "Batch failed ({e}) and rollback failed ({rollback_err}). State may be inconsistent."
                    )));
                }
                Err(e)
            }
        }
    }
}
```

Re-export from `lib.rs`:
```rust
pub use backend::Backend;
```

