# Define the generic Command trait

## Motivation
Kanban-domain's `Command` enum exposes inherent methods (`execute`, `capture_inverse`, `description`) — see `crates/kanban-domain/src/commands/mod.rs:32-71`. There's no actual trait today. To let the generic `Context<B, Cmd>` dispatch commands without knowing what `Cmd` is, we need an abstract trait in kanban-core.

## Current state
Placeholder file at `crates/kanban-core/src/command.rs` from Scaffolding. No `Command` trait exists anywhere.

## Target shape
```rust
//! Generic, reversible domain command.
//!
//! Implemented by the consumer's top-level command type (e.g.
//! `kanban_domain::commands::Command` or `output::SrsCommand`).
//! The generic `Context<B, Cmd>` only sees this trait surface.

use crate::CoreResult;

pub trait Command: Clone + Send + Sync + 'static {
    /// Execution context borrowed from the backend for this dispatch.
    /// GAT lets the lifetime tie to the Backend ref.
    type Ctx<'a>;

    /// Read-only store for inverse capture. `?Sized` so it can be a
    /// trait object (e.g. `dyn DataStore`).
    type Store: ?Sized + 'static;

    /// Apply this command. Mutating side-effects land via `ctx`'s
    /// interior-mutability handle (or the consumer's chosen mutation
    /// strategy).
    fn execute(&self, ctx: &Self::Ctx<'_>) -> CoreResult<()>;

    /// Build the rollback batch by reading pre-state from `store`.
    /// **Called BEFORE `execute` runs**, so the returned commands see
    /// the world as it was before this command's mutation.
    /// Empty Vec = no-op to undo. Err = inverse cannot be captured.
    fn capture_inverse(&self, store: &Self::Store) -> CoreResult<Vec<Self>>;
}
```

Re-export from `lib.rs`:
```rust
pub use command::Command;
```

## Steps
1. Replace placeholder body in `crates/kanban-core/src/command.rs` with the trait above plus module-level doc explaining design choices (why `Vec<Self>` not `type Inverse`, why GAT).
2. Add `pub use command::Command;` to `lib.rs`.
3. Add unit tests verifying a `MockCommand` impl compiles.

## Alternatives (mentioned in section card)
- `type Inverse: Command<Ctx>` — rejected; kanban's inverses are heterogeneous.
- `Box<dyn Command<Ctx>>` — kills serde round-trip.

## Edge cases
- GAT (`type Ctx<'a>`) stable since Rust 1.65. Workspace already uses GATs (see kanban-core/src/graph/).
- The `Clone + 'static` bound on `Cmd` is what lets UndoStack push it for later redo. Don't drop it.
- `Self: Sized` is implicit from the `Vec<Self>` return; trait isn't object-safe. Kanban never uses `dyn Command` (always through the typed enum); revisit `?Sized` only if a future consumer needs trait-object commands.

