# The heart of the refactor: generic execute pipeline

## Motivation
`Context::execute` is the load-bearing method. Body is a port of `KanbanContext::execute` (`crates/kanban-service/src/context.rs:191-214`) with type substitutions: `KanbanResult → CoreResult`, `Vec<Command> → Vec<Cmd>`, `backend.as_data_store() → backend.store()`, `CommandContext { store } → backend.ctx()`, `backend.append_commands(cmds) → backend.append_to_audit(cmds)`.

Three invariants must be preserved:
1. **Capture before execute** — `capture_inverse` reads pre-state, must run before mutation.
2. **Reverse-then-flatten composition** — `(F1; F2; F3)^-1 = F3^-1; F2^-1; F1^-1`.
3. **Single transaction** — capture + execute + audit append all run inside `with_transaction`; any failure rolls the batch back.

## Current state
`crates/kanban-service/src/context.rs:191-214`:
```rust
pub fn execute(&mut self, commands: Vec<Command>) -> KanbanResult<()> {
    let backend = Arc::clone(&self.backend);
    let cmds = &commands;
    let mut per_cmd_inverses: Vec<Vec<Command>> = Vec::new();
    self.backend.with_transaction(&mut || {
        let store: &dyn DataStore = backend.as_data_store();
        let ctx = CommandContext { store };
        for cmd in cmds.iter() {
            per_cmd_inverses.push(cmd.capture_inverse(store)?);
            cmd.execute(&ctx)?;
        }
        backend.append_commands(cmds)?;
        Ok(())
    })?;
    let inverses: Vec<Command> = per_cmd_inverses.into_iter().rev().flatten().collect();
    self.undo_stack.push(UndoEntry { forward: commands, inverse: inverses });
    self.dirty = true;
    Ok(())
}
```

## Target shape
Add to `crates/kanban-core/src/context.rs`:

```rust
impl<B, Cmd> Context<B, Cmd>
where
    B: Backend + BackendExecutor<Cmd> + ?Sized,
    Cmd: Command,
{
    /// Execute a batch as one undo unit. Capture + execute + audit
    /// append run inside one transaction; any failure rolls the batch
    /// back. The composed inverse (per-command inverses reversed and
    /// flattened) is pushed onto the undo stack.
    pub fn execute(&mut self, commands: Vec<Cmd>) -> CoreResult<()> {
        let backend = Arc::clone(&self.backend);
        let cmds = &commands;
        let mut per_cmd_inverses: Vec<Vec<Cmd>> = Vec::new();
        self.backend.with_transaction(&mut || {
            let store = backend.store();
            let ctx = backend.ctx();
            for cmd in cmds.iter() {
                per_cmd_inverses.push(cmd.capture_inverse(store)?);
                cmd.execute(&ctx)?;
            }
            backend.append_to_audit(cmds)?;
            Ok(())
        })?;
        let inverses: Vec<Cmd> = per_cmd_inverses
            .into_iter()
            .rev()
            .flatten()
            .collect();
        self.undo_stack.push(UndoEntry { forward: commands, inverse: inverses });
        self.dirty = true;
        Ok(())
    }
}
```

