# Generic undo and redo through the inverse-replay pattern

## Motivation
Undo and redo mirror each other: peek the appropriate entry, replay the stored Vec<Cmd> through the same transaction primitive, commit the cursor on success. Ports `KanbanContext::undo` (`context.rs:219-234`) and `redo` (`context.rs:239-254`) with type substitutions.

## Current state (KanbanContext::undo at context.rs:219-234)
```rust
pub fn undo(&mut self) -> KanbanResult<bool> {
    let inverse = match self.undo_stack.peek_undo() {
        Some(e) => e.inverse.clone(),
        None => return Ok(false),
    };
    let backend = Arc::clone(&self.backend);
    let inv = &inverse;
    self.backend.with_transaction(&mut || {
        let store = backend.as_data_store();
        let ctx = CommandContext { store };
        inv.iter().try_for_each(|cmd| cmd.execute(&ctx))
    })?;
    self.undo_stack.commit_undo();
    self.dirty = true;
    Ok(true)
}
```

Redo is symmetric: `peek_redo` → `entry.forward.clone()` → same transaction body → `commit_redo`.

## Target shape
Add to `crates/kanban-core/src/context.rs` (alongside `execute`):

```rust
pub fn undo(&mut self) -> CoreResult<bool> {
    let inverse = match self.undo_stack.peek_undo() {
        Some(e) => e.inverse.clone(),
        None => return Ok(false),
    };
    let backend = Arc::clone(&self.backend);
    let inv = &inverse;
    self.backend.with_transaction(&mut || {
        let ctx = backend.ctx();
        inv.iter().try_for_each(|cmd| cmd.execute(&ctx))
    })?;
    self.undo_stack.commit_undo();
    self.dirty = true;
    Ok(true)
}

pub fn redo(&mut self) -> CoreResult<bool> {
    let forward = match self.undo_stack.peek_redo() {
        Some(e) => e.forward.clone(),
        None => return Ok(false),
    };
    let backend = Arc::clone(&self.backend);
    let fwd = &forward;
    self.backend.with_transaction(&mut || {
        let ctx = backend.ctx();
        fwd.iter().try_for_each(|cmd| cmd.execute(&ctx))
    })?;
    self.undo_stack.commit_redo();
    self.dirty = true;
    Ok(true)
}
```

## Steps
1. Confirm Context skeleton (5.1) + execute (5.2) merged.
2. Add `undo` and `redo` methods.
3. Add unit tests (see Tests).
4. `cargo test -p kanban-core context::tests::test_undo* context::tests::test_redo*`.

## Edge cases
- `Ok(false)` (not `Err`) when nothing to undo/redo — matches existing semantics. The boolean signals "actually did something" vs "no-op".
- `commit_undo`/`commit_redo` are only called AFTER `with_transaction` succeeds. If the transaction fails, the cursor stays where it was, so a retry sees the same entry.
- `entry.inverse.clone()` — `Cmd: Clone` is required (already in the trait bound).
- Important: undo/redo do NOT call `append_to_audit`. They replay history, not new history.

