# Split SqliteBackend: Backend (lifecycle) + KanbanBackend (kanban extras)

## Motivation
`SqliteBackend` (`crates/kanban-service/src/sqlite_backend.rs:199-229`) currently implements `KanbanBackend` directly with `flush`, `instance_id`, `persistence_metadata`. After the trait split (card 6.1), the lifecycle methods belong to `Backend`. This card splits the monolithic impl into two blocks.

## Current state
`crates/kanban-service/src/sqlite_backend.rs:199-229`:
```rust
#[async_trait]
impl KanbanBackend for SqliteBackend {
    fn as_data_store(&self) -> &dyn DataStore { self }

    async fn flush(&self) -> KanbanResult<()> {
        self.db.stamp_writer().await?;
        self.db.checkpoint().await?;
        let fresh = self.db.read_metadata_sync()?;
        let mut guard = self.last_metadata.write()
            .map_err(|_| KanbanError::Internal("sqlite_backend: last_metadata RwLock poisoned".into()))?;
        *guard = fresh;
        Ok(())
    }

    fn instance_id(&self) -> Uuid {
        <SqliteStore as PersistenceStore>::instance_id(&self.db)
    }

    fn persistence_metadata(&self) -> Option<PersistenceMetadata> {
        self.last_metadata.read().ok().and_then(|g| g.clone())
    }
}
```

## Target shape
```rust
use kanban_core::{Backend, CoreError, CoreResult};

#[async_trait]
impl Backend for SqliteBackend {
    type Snapshot = kanban_domain::Snapshot;

    fn snapshot(&self) -> CoreResult<Self::Snapshot> {
        DataStore::snapshot(self).map_err(CoreError::from)
    }

    fn apply_snapshot(&self, s: Self::Snapshot) -> CoreResult<()> {
        DataStore::apply_snapshot(self, s).map_err(CoreError::from)
    }

    async fn flush(&self) -> CoreResult<()> {
        // Wrap the kanban-side body so KanbanResult errors map via the
        // From<KanbanError> for CoreError impl from Scaffolding.
        let inner = async {
            self.db.stamp_writer().await?;
            self.db.checkpoint().await?;
            let fresh = self.db.read_metadata_sync()?;
            let mut guard = self.last_metadata.write()
                .map_err(|_| KanbanError::Internal("sqlite_backend: last_metadata RwLock poisoned".into()))?;
            *guard = fresh;
            Ok::<_, KanbanError>(())
        };
        inner.await.map_err(CoreError::from)
    }

    fn instance_id(&self) -> Uuid {
        <SqliteStore as PersistenceStore>::instance_id(&self.db)
    }
    // needs_flush / needs_save_worker / reload use Backend defaults
    // (write-through: reads are always live, no save worker needed).
}

#[async_trait]
impl KanbanBackend for SqliteBackend {
    fn as_data_store(&self) -> &dyn DataStore { self }

    fn persistence_metadata(&self) -> Option<PersistenceMetadata> {
        self.last_metadata.read().ok().and_then(|g| g.clone())
    }
}
```

