# Split JsonBackend: Backend (lifecycle + dirty flag) + KanbanBackend (extras)

## Motivation
Mirror of card 6.2 for `JsonDataStore`. JSON is the more interesting case: it has a dirty flag, a background save worker, and a custom `reload()` that resets the lazy cache.

## Current state
`crates/kanban-service/src/json_backend.rs:319-367`:
```rust
#[async_trait]
impl KanbanBackend for JsonDataStore {
    fn as_data_store(&self) -> &dyn DataStore { self }

    async fn flush(&self) -> KanbanResult<()> {
        if !self.dirty.swap(false, Ordering::AcqRel) { return Ok(()); }
        let result = self.do_flush().await;
        if result.is_err() { self.dirty.store(true, Ordering::Release); }
        result
    }

    async fn reload(&self) -> KanbanResult<()> { /* clear inner; reset dirty */ }
    fn needs_flush(&self) -> bool { self.dirty.load(Ordering::Acquire) }
    fn needs_save_worker(&self) -> bool { true }
    fn instance_id(&self) -> Uuid { self.file_store.instance_id() }
    fn persistence_metadata(&self) -> Option<PersistenceMetadata> { ... }
}
```

## Target shape
```rust
use kanban_core::{Backend, CoreError, CoreResult};

#[async_trait]
impl Backend for JsonDataStore {
    type Snapshot = kanban_domain::Snapshot;

    fn snapshot(&self) -> CoreResult<Self::Snapshot> {
        DataStore::snapshot(self).map_err(CoreError::from)
    }

    fn apply_snapshot(&self, s: Self::Snapshot) -> CoreResult<()> {
        DataStore::apply_snapshot(self, s).map_err(CoreError::from)
    }

    async fn flush(&self) -> CoreResult<()> {
        if !self.dirty.swap(false, Ordering::AcqRel) { return Ok(()); }
        match self.do_flush().await {
            Ok(()) => Ok(()),
            Err(e) => {
                self.dirty.store(true, Ordering::Release);
                Err(CoreError::from(e))
            }
        }
    }

    async fn reload(&self) -> CoreResult<()> {
        {
            let mut guard = self.inner.write().map_err(|_| {
                CoreError::Internal("json_backend: inner RwLock poisoned".into())
            })?;
            *guard = None;
        }
        self.dirty.store(false, Ordering::Release);
        Ok(())
    }

    fn needs_flush(&self) -> bool { self.dirty.load(Ordering::Acquire) }
    fn needs_save_worker(&self) -> bool { true }
    fn instance_id(&self) -> Uuid { self.file_store.instance_id() }
}

#[async_trait]
impl KanbanBackend for JsonDataStore {
    fn as_data_store(&self) -> &dyn DataStore { self }

    fn persistence_metadata(&self) -> Option<PersistenceMetadata> {
        self.last_metadata.read().ok().and_then(|g| g.clone())
    }
}
```

