# Hoist atomic-write + config-dir + format-dispatch helpers to kanban-core

## Motivation
`crates/kanban-service/src/config.rs` (1100+ lines) mixes three concerns: (1) AppConfig-specific stripping/DTO, (2) config file I/O scaffolding, (3) platform-specific config-dir resolution. The latter two are purely generic — Output's SRS app needs the same atomic write + 0o600 perms + `~/.config/<app>/config.toml` pattern.

## Current state
Three generic blocks in `crates/kanban-service/src/config.rs`:

(a) Lines 8-25 — `config_path()` hardcoded to "kanban" in 3 cfg branches.
(b) Lines 362-381 — `write_config_file()` atomic write via `tempfile::NamedTempFile::persist` + 0o600 on unix.
(c) Lines 35-61 + 74-91 — `load_from()`/`save_to()` format dispatch on file extension.

## Target shape
Replace placeholder in `crates/kanban-core/src/config_io.rs`:

```rust
//! Cross-platform config file I/O scaffolding.
use crate::{CoreError, CoreResult};
use serde::{de::DeserializeOwned, Serialize};
use std::path::{Path, PathBuf};

pub fn config_path_for_app(app_name: &str) -> Option<PathBuf> {
    #[cfg(target_os = "macos")]
    { dirs::home_dir().map(|h| h.join(".config").join(app_name).join("config.toml")) }
    #[cfg(target_os = "linux")]
    { dirs::config_dir().map(|c| c.join(app_name).join("config.toml")) }
    #[cfg(target_os = "windows")]
    { dirs::config_dir().map(|c| c.join(app_name).join("config.toml")) }
    #[cfg(not(any(target_os = "macos", target_os = "linux", target_os = "windows")))]
    { None }
}

pub fn atomic_write(path: &Path, content: &str) -> std::io::Result<()> {
    let parent = path.parent().unwrap_or_else(|| Path::new("."));
    let mut tmp = tempfile::NamedTempFile::new_in(parent)?;
    #[cfg(unix)]
    {
        use std::os::unix::fs::PermissionsExt;
        tmp.as_file().set_permissions(std::fs::Permissions::from_mode(0o600))?;
    }
    std::io::Write::write_all(&mut tmp, content.as_bytes())?;
    tmp.persist(path).map_err(|e| e.error)?;
    Ok(())
}

pub fn load_or_default<T: DeserializeOwned + Default>(path: &Path) -> T {
    try_load(path).unwrap_or_default()
}

pub fn try_load<T: DeserializeOwned>(path: &Path) -> CoreResult<T> {
    let content = std::fs::read_to_string(path)
        .map_err(|e| CoreError::Config(format!("Failed to read config: {e}")))?;
    let ext = path.extension().and_then(|e| e.to_str()).unwrap_or("");
    match ext {
        "json" => serde_json::from_str(&content)
            .map_err(|e| CoreError::Config(format!("Failed to parse JSON config: {e}"))),
        _ => toml::from_str(&content)
            .map_err(|e| CoreError::Config(format!("Failed to parse TOML config: {e}"))),
    }
}

pub fn save<T: Serialize>(value: &T, path: &Path) -> CoreResult<()> {
    if let Some(parent) = path.parent() {
        std::fs::create_dir_all(parent)
            .map_err(|e| CoreError::Config(format!("Failed to create config dir: {e}")))?;
    }
    let ext = path.extension().and_then(|e| e.to_str()).unwrap_or("");
    let content = match ext {
        "json" => serde_json::to_string_pretty(value)
            .map_err(|e| CoreError::Config(format!("Failed to serialize: {e}")))?,
        _ => toml::to_string_pretty(value)
            .map_err(|e| CoreError::Config(format!("Failed to serialize: {e}")))?,
    };
    atomic_write(path, &content).map_err(|e| CoreError::Config(format!("Failed to write: {e}")))?;
    Ok(())
}
```

